File: Zambia's former President Rupiah Banda (R) waves to supporters. AFP PHOTO / CHIBALA ZULU CHIBALA ZULU / AFP JOHANNESBURG -  Former Zambian President, Rupiah Banda, has died aged 85. Banda was the country's fourth democratically elected President and led Zambia from 2008 until 2011. READ: Zambia's leader says turning around economy, despite empty coffers He was diagnosed with colon cancer in 2020. During Banda's presidency, he worked to strengthen the country’s economy as well as the healthcare and education sectors. 